details.description: Founded in 1992 in Taipei, Taiwan, Sharetea is a leading global bubble tea brand serving premiere authentic bubble tea. We offer a wide variety of fresh, high-quality drinks that blend premium tea with perfectly crafted tapioca pearls and other delicious toppings. Sharetea’s menu features an extensive range of beverages, including classic milk teas, premium fruit teas, and refreshing slushes. Our drinks come in a variety of customizable options, allowing customers to adjust sweetness levels, ice amounts, and toppings to suit their personal preferences. Whether you're craving one of our delectable milk teas, refreshing fruit teas, or savory slushes, we have the drink for you!

It's the kind of place where the service goes beyond friendly—it’s genuinely welcoming. He takes the time to ask how you're doing and remembers your favorite drink, which is a rare and thoughtful touch.
Not only are the boba teas here absolutely delicious, with a wide variety of flavors and toppings to choose from, but it's the personal connection that makes every visit special. Dave has created a space where everyone feels like they’re part of the family, and you can sense the community he's built. It’s that extra bit of warmth that keeps me coming back, time and time again. If you want great drinks and an even better experience, this is the spot!

Edit to response: We drove 4 mins up the road for the exact same fruit tea for $3 cheaper ($4.50) including toppings which were an additional $0.81 at ShareTea; not exactly market value. reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Lauren, thanks for the review. As the owner I can assure you our prices have not doubled since we opened. That is false. Prices are in line with the local and national markets. Doubled price would suggest a Fruit Tea was once $3.65; which it was not. We have several Fruit Teas on the menu (e.g. Wintermelon, Strawberry, and Mango) available in the $6 range today pre- tax. Wintermelon Tea is $5.03 and Wintermelon Lemonade is $6.76, not the $7.30 price you are suggesting. That pricing is transparent on Doordash, Grubhub, UberEats, and Clover as well as on our Kiosk and POS system in-store. All of the pricing is synced. 

Note, to preserve authenticity our ingredients are imported from Taiwan which comes with additional costs to our small business. There are local domestic boba tea shops that source ingredients from generic wholesalers which may marginally impact relative price point making them cheaper. In short, the quality of Mango Fruit Tea may vary depending on where you buy it. Also, it seems like you are including sales tax in your pricing of $7.50 and have left several 1 star reviews on other businesses. As a locally owned family run small business we would appreciate if you spoke to quality and experience in the store as well as it relates to the overall review as opposed to solely mis-characterizing our pricing and offerings.

We are not aware of any comparable Fruit Tea for $4.50 that includes toppings in the local market, especially within 4 minutes of our store, but are glad that you found something that meets your expectations and do hope you will give Sharetea Cornelius another try. That said, we stand behind the quality of our drinks and the associated pricing and would refer guests to our many 5 star reviews.

Why not go here? Overly complicated menu. Ridiculous kiosk right in front of counter staff. You actually pay a premium to use the kiosk and pay by credit card. STUPID. If you order with a staff member and pay cash you receive a discount.

All in all a good drink. Try new things.

reviews_data.review_text:
Prices significantly higher on kiosk than on the screen. $7.50 for a medium fruit tea (no add-ons) is actually ridiculous. How have prices doubled since you opened?

Edit to response: We drove 4 mins up the road for the exact same fruit tea for $3 cheaper ($4.50) including toppings which were an additional $0.81 at ShareTea; not exactly market value. I have gotten the wintermelon fruit tea from ShareTea since you opened and it was not this price. $7.30 w/o tax on the kiosk today but around a dollar less (still w/o tax) on the board that everyone was looking at.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Lauren, thanks for the review. As the owner I can assure you our prices have not doubled since we opened. That is false. Prices are in line with the local and national markets. Doubled price would suggest a Fruit Tea was once $3.65; which it was not. We have several Fruit Teas on the menu (e.g. Wintermelon, Strawberry, and Mango) available in the $6 range today pre- tax. Wintermelon Tea is $5.03 and Wintermelon Lemonade is $6.76, not the $7.30 price you are suggesting. That pricing is transparent on Doordash, Grubhub, UberEats, and Clover as well as on our Kiosk and POS system in-store. All of the pricing is synced. 

Note, to preserve authenticity our ingredients are imported from Taiwan which comes with additional costs to our small business. There are local domestic boba tea shops that source ingredients from generic wholesalers which may marginally impact relative price point making them cheaper. In short, the quality of Mango Fruit Tea may vary depending on where you buy it. Also, it seems like you are including sales tax in your pricing of $7.50 and have left several 1 star reviews on other businesses. As a locally owned family run small business we would appreciate if you spoke to quality and experience in the store as well as it relates to the overall review as opposed to solely mis-characterizing our pricing and offerings.

We are not aware of any comparable Fruit Tea for $4.50 that includes toppings in the local market, especially within 4 minutes of our store, but are glad that you found something that meets your expectations and do hope you will give Sharetea Cornelius another try. That said, we stand behind the quality of our drinks and the associated pricing and would refer guests to our many 5 star reviews.

reviews_data.review_text: Great experience and awesome tea options!

Love this place! Was traveling and stopped by to get my bubble tea fix. I tried the mango bubble tea and it was absolutely delicious. The employees were friendly and the place was very clean inside. Will definitely come back in the future.

Excellent customer service and very friendly. However, they need better training. I ordered Taro and got nothing but white milk, 3 times! Check the picture for reference. The drink should be purple and should taste like taro. I would highly recommend B&K cafe in Mooresville, or Joel’s Asian grill, they actually put flavors that you can taste and see! For $5 instead of $8 for milk! (Put more powder) we’re paying more than enough for that. Thanks!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Eddie,

Thanks for the review. I did speak to our staff and understand they remade the drink on multiple occasions to accommodate you adding in more Taro than our standard recipe. Our taro is made with authentic ingredients imported from Taiwan and the measurements are the same in every drink. I have had other local boba and would describe most of that taro on heavier & sweeter side as compared with Sharetea. My guess is their ingredients are domestic as well. Perhaps that’s what you were expecting. 

The lighting in your photo is distorted as the drink is more purple and I have never seen it otherwise. Our employees confirmed the drink was made correctly but am sorry it did not meet your taste satisfaction. We of course cannot please everyone’s palate but our product is premium as compared to local alternatives in the market and consistent with exception to the rare occasion. 

Thanks again.

reviews_data.review_text:
Overall 3 stars. With very little effort this store would easily be 4 stars.

Why go here? Interesting drink menu. Great flavors.

Why not go here? Overly complicated menu. Ridiculous kiosk right in front of counter staff. You actually pay a premium to use the kiosk and pay by credit card. STUPID. If you order with a staff member and pay cash you receive a discount.

What else ? Confusing if one is not familiar with Boba teas. I had no idea if I should ask for more or less ice. No idea if I would like 50% sweet or more or even what add ins were available or would complement the mango and passion fruit tea.  A step by step card or menu would have been so helpful.
The counter person was helpful only because I was clueless.

In the end ordered mango with passion fruit with medium ice and no additional sweetener. The drink was super good 👍. In fact amazing. The only negative is the seeds from the passion fruit could easily be aspirated sucking through a straw. I choked a little and then learned.

All in all a good drink. Try new things.

Store owner advice…a little cleaner store and seriously dump the kiosk it severely detracts from the customer experience.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thanks for the feedback! Store ownership recently changed and you will notice that we moved the kiosk a good distance away from the cashier to give guests to ability to order from either the register or the Kiosk, whichever is preferred. 

We will assuredly coach our Bobaristas on walking guests through the menu. Although large with several flavors and options once a guest is coached through the menu you will find its easy to mix and match was you like to purchase your go-to favorite or try something new!

Mango passion fruit is one of our favorites!

Hope to see you in again soon!

reviews_data.review_text:
I do not enjoy using the kiosk to order - especially when there are 3+ employees behind the counter who could be assisting (they stood/sat and watched while we ordered).  The menu is complex with many options, so kiosk is not ideal.

Loud music with obscenities played while we were there last - not an enjoyable experience as a parent with a child present.

We always enjoy the drinks but the service has declined over the last few months.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Derek, thanks for the review. My wife and I recently took ownership of the store and agree with sentiment on the music. We are also a parents and obscene music has no place in the restaurant. The team has recently been coached on this. Sharetea is a family friendly establishment and we intend to ensure we provide that experience. Sorry to hear about the order experience. We change policy now enabling guests to pay at either the Kiosk or the register, whichever is preferred. We did keep the kiosk for guests that prefer it and wish to navigate the menu. 

Please look for service improvement your next time in and we hope to see you again soon!
